# TROUBLESHOOTING

| Symptom | Likely cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `Run aborted: lock held by run-…` | Prior run did not release lock | Check `.audit/state/locks/run.lock`; if PID is dead, delete the file. |
| `No findings in 0 files` | `SCOPE` matched nothing, or all files excluded | Check `SCOPE` and `config.yaml.exclusions`. |
| Same finding keeps reappearing after `WONT_DO` | Fingerprint changed (paths or symbols renamed) | Inspect both fingerprints in `wont-do.json` vs `index.json`; add the new fingerprint manually with a note. |
| Daily file has duplicate findings under different IDs | Two concurrent runs raced (lock missed) | Run consolidate mode; verify lock works on your runner. |
| Execute refuses an `APPROVED` item | Type is in `execute.block_types`, OR risk gate triggered | Check Run Summary `errors[]`; flip type or remove from block list if intentional. |
| Reports say `no_git: true` but `.git` exists | `git` binary not on PATH for the runner | Install git or add it to the runner image. |
| Run Summary shows `truncated: true` | Hit `max_runtime_minutes` | Raise the limit, narrow `SCOPE`, or split scanners across runs. |
| Index file > 5 MB and slow to read | Rotation threshold reached | Run `MODE=consolidate`; rotation is automatic. |
